{"title":"When Will China Qualify for the World Cup?","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"When Will China Qualify for the World Cup?","format":{"revealjs":{"theme":"sky","slide-number":true,"embed-resources":true}}},"headingText":"Current Situation 🇨🇳","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\nChina has struggled to qualify for the FIFA World Cup in recent years.\n\n- Last appearance: 2002 World Cup\n- Strong competition in Asia (Japan, Korea, Iran)\n- Need for long-term development\n\n### Key Challenges\n- Youth training system\n- Coaching quality\n- International experience\n\n---\n\n## Future Outlook 🔍\n\nChina is investing more in football development.\n\n- More youth academies\n- Government support for sports\n- Increasing popularity of football\n\n### Possible Timeline\n- Short term (2026): Low probability\n- Medium term (2030): Possible qualification\n- Long term (2034+): More realistic\n\n---\n\n## My Prediction 🏆\n\nChina could qualify for the World Cup around **2030–2034**.\n\n### Reasons\n- Improved youth development\n- More exposure to international competition\n- Gradual improvement in league quality\n\n### Conclusion\nWith consistent effort and investment, China has the potential to return to the World Cup stage in the next decade.\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n## Current Situation 🇨🇳\n\nChina has struggled to qualify for the FIFA World Cup in recent years.\n\n- Last appearance: 2002 World Cup\n- Strong competition in Asia (Japan, Korea, Iran)\n- Need for long-term development\n\n### Key Challenges\n- Youth training system\n- Coaching quality\n- International experience\n\n---\n\n## Future Outlook 🔍\n\nChina is investing more in football development.\n\n- More youth academies\n- Government support for sports\n- Increasing popularity of football\n\n### Possible Timeline\n- Short term (2026): Low probability\n- Medium term (2030): Possible qualification\n- Long term (2034+): More realistic\n\n---\n\n## My Prediction 🏆\n\nChina could qualify for the World Cup around 